  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study tests the effectiveness of the bilingual Health and Success program, which aims to
      support Latino parents and schools in their efforts to promote the academic success and
      healthy choices of youth, with the goal of reducing barriers that lead to elevated levels of
      HIV/AIDS in urban Latino communities.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
